I am thrilled to announce that I have successfully completed my training in Data Science with Machine Learning and Python. This intensive program has equipped me with the latest skills and knowledge needed to excel in the field of Data Science and Machine Learning.

Over the course of the program, I gained hands-on experience working with a variety of tools and techniques, including Python, NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Scikit-Learn. I also learned how to apply advanced statistical methods and machine learning algorithms to real-world problems, such as predictive modeling, data visualization. 

I would like to thank the program organizers Saheel Ramji  and instructors Rishav Das ↗️  for their dedication  and expertise.

Hello connections, 

I had the privilege to attend an incredible event organized by Orkes and Zone Startup, focused on the world of microservices and distributed applications. The event featured industry experts who shared their insights on cutting-edge technologies and real-world applications. 

The event kicked off with an enlightening session on "Monitoring Infrastructure and Microservices with Elastic Observability" by the esteemed
Ashish Tiwari  from Elastic. Ashish sir delved into the importance of observability in a distributed environment and how Elastic's tools can help monitor and troubleshoot complex microservices architectures effectively. 

Next up, we had the pleasure of hearing from Manan Bhatt, shared his expertise on "Building Event Driven Distributed Applications with Conductor." He explored the power of event-driven architectures and how Conductor, a powerful orchestration engine, can simplify the development and management of such applications. .

I would like to extend my heartfelt gratitude to Zone Startup for organizing such an enlightening event. 

#ZoneStartup #Microservices #DistributedApplications #EventRecap #ElasticObservability #Conductor #NetflixConductor #TechnologyAdvancements

Hi everyone,

I am excited to share my recent experience at the HackOverflow  1.0 National level hackathon organized by CSI PHCET . The hackathon was 36 hours long and took place in offline mode. Our team Lokesh Patil , Chaitali Padalkar , Yashraj Mundada  participated and made it to the #top20 teams out of 70 teams!
 
Although we didn't win,but the experience was invaluable. We learned so many new things and had the opportunity to meet young minds from different states and cities who were experts in different technologies. It was inspiring to see so many people come together and work towards a common goal.

I am grateful for the opportunity to participate in this hackathon and for the knowledge and experience gained from it.Thank you to our judge Anjani Kumar Thakur for knowledge you shared with us. 

Thank you to CSI PHCET  and HackOverflow  for giving us this opportunity and organizing this fantastic event 

 #event #hackathon #hackoverflow #phcet #team #coding #team #opportunity #experience #top20

Hii connections, 

I m glad to share that I have successfully completed my Future Ready Talent Internship Which is provided  by Microsoft  through Future Ready Talent Program organized in association with FutureSkills Prime nasscom  FutureSkills  and AICTE 


During my internship period, I had the incredible opportunity to dive deep into the world of Microsoft Azure cloud services and gain hands-on experience with Azure Portal. 

One of the highlights of my internship was working with Microsoft Azure services and implement those services in my project, which opened up a whole new realm of possibilities for me.In particular, I work with Web App Services for seamless deployment and Azure Cosmos DB for efficient data storage in the database. 

I would like to express my sincere gratitude to the entire Future Ready Talent Internship program,Microsoft , GitHub ,  nasscom , AICTE , EY , and Microsoft Learn  for this incredible opportunity . 


#MicrosoftInternship #AzureServices #FutureReadyTalent #LifelongLearner
 #experience #azure #project #internship #github #microsoftazure

Hello connection...
Me and my team lokesh patil, Tejaswi Jadhav  and anuja landge had recently participated in "Vodafone Intelligent Solutions for the Tech Innovation Marathon 2022" supported by Vodafone Idea Foundation and Connecting dreams organized boot camps, hackathons, and conversations with experts from the industry to boost young entrepreneurs' zeal to innovate in the real-world context. My team got selected for the finals of the Innovation Marathon 2022 on a National Level where I represented my team as a Team Leader at Pune for showcase of my project prototype..

So past two days were one of the best days of my life, the experience with _VOIS , Connecting Dreams Foundation  and Vodafone Foundation has been one of the most mesmerizing events.  I met a lot of new people each having unique personality and a great mindset. We were in the Top 40 finalists, though we did not win the finals it still was a great achievement. Meeting different students from different universities, different streams, and also the jury actively taking interest in conversation with us. 

Thank you Megha Goja , sayed namra and poovaragavan velumani for guiding us and mentoring us throughout the program.. Thank u to whole vois team for providing such a great opportunity to connect, learn and grow with an amazing platform.

#vodafoneideafoundation #vois #connectingdreams #innovation #opportunity #team
